{"id":24248,"title":"[Hospital hygiene - Where are we in the sixth year of \"Operation Clean Hands\"?].","abstract":"The national German hand hygiene campaign is implementing the WHO patient safety initiative \"Clean Care is Safer Care\". After 6 years over 1400 health care institutions are participating in the campaign on a voluntary basis. The implementation of the multimodal intervention concept including improvement of alcohol based hand rub availability, the introduction of 2 surveillance methods and of the WHO \"My 5 Moments of Hand Hygiene Model\" in those health care facilities, participating for several years, increased median hand hygiene compliance by 11% and alcohol based hand rub availability by 61%. ","date":"2014-01-21","categories":"Bacterial Infections and Mycoses","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24446006","annotations":[{"name":"Health care","weight":0.804197,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Health_care"},{"name":"Hospital","weight":0.783378,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hospital"},{"name":"Health","weight":0.734333,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Health"},{"name":"World Health Organization","weight":0.706565,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Health_Organization"},{"name":"Hygiene","weight":0.654271,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hygiene"},{"name":"Alcohol","weight":0.550591,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alcohol"},{"name":"Germany","weight":0.485251,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Germany"},{"name":"Patient","weight":0.322201,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient"},{"name":"Volunteering","weight":0.282308,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Volunteering"},{"name":"Health care provider","weight":0.281281,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Health_care_provider"},{"name":"Patient safety","weight":0.148948,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.